It's time you cool your anger and take care of your inner self.

250
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:52,290
My inner self is already well-kept.

251
00:17:52,290 --> 00:17:54,450
Choi Won. It's you who needs to listen.

252
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:58,450
No matter how many times you attack my age, it's useless.

253
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:03,970
Why? Because I'm a successful marketing director with a perfect boyfriend, and am soon to be married,

254
00:18:03,970 --> 00:18:08,990
while you haven't had a girlfriend for three years, and will probably not have one, because you're like a squid.

255
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:12,410
Wow, what a cheap shot. Fine, you're a know-it-all.

256
00:18:12,410 --> 00:18:14,170
Couple's Heaven. Single's Hell. Alright?

257
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:15,900
Ah, really.

258
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:20,460
I called you to ask you to buy me eye cream at the duty-free shop.

259
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:23,140
Do I have to argue with you whenever I call you?

260
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,640
You eye-cream addict.

261
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,510
When are you coming?

262
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:29,470
I don't know. I have to check the flight schedule.

263
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:34,300
Hang up... Hello?

264
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,810
Hey, did you hang up?

265
00:18:37,810 --> 00:18:39,210
Won.

266
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:41,110
What?

267
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:45,690
My boyfriend didn't put 'I love you' on my birthday card

268
00:18:45,690 --> 00:18:49,360
and just put 'Happy Birthday,' so I'm a little sad.

269
00:18:50,530 --> 00:18:53,050
Am I overreacting?

270
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:54,330
No.

271
00:18:54,330 --> 00:18:56,760
Then? Has our relationship gone cold now?

272
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,960
Has it gone cold now....?

273
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,540
It's what he wants you to think so he can propose!

274
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:04,960
Isn't that what he's going for? Looks like the guy's a player.

275
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:09,080
A player? Yeah, right. Alright then.

276
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:11,070
Thanks.

277
00:19:39,430 --> 00:19:41,290
Are you okay?!

278
00:19:41,290 --> 00:19:42,470
Our little chicks seemed to have arrived!

279
00:19:42,470 --> 00:19:44,190
Yes. Hello!

280
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:45,520
Yeah.

281
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,900
Hello. I'm an intern stewardess, Lee So Eun.

282
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:51,270
It's an honor to be on the same flight crew.

283
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:54,550
Teacher, I was a fan of yours since I was in school.

284
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:59,430
Teacher? This isn't a school. Be sure to call me by my title.

285
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:00,390
I'm sorry.

286
00:20:00,390 --> 00:20:03,500
Ah, I really hate hearing the word teacher.

287
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:08,260
Ah, Miss Choi, really.

288
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:13,680
Attention, all guests. I will now give instructions on the use of the emergency equipment and the emergency exit.

289
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:17,630
Ladies and Gentlemen. This is the passenger safety briefing.

290
00:20:17,630 --> 00:20:20,340
In case of an emergency, the emergency exits are located

291
00:20:20,340 --> 00:20:23,630
on the left and right, as shown by the stewardesses.

292
00:20:23,630 --> 00:20:28,210
There are eight exits in the aircraft for emergency evacuation.

293
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:32,150
When exiting through the emergency exits, please follow the emergency lights in the walkways.

294
00:20:32,150 --> 00:20:37,620
In case of emergency evacuation, please follow the emergency lights in the cabin.

295
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:42,520
Clasp both sides of  he seat belt together and tighten.

296
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:45,220
In order to release, pull the top of the buckle upward.

297
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:51,320
To fasten the seat belt, insert the metal tongue into the buckle and pull the loose end for tightening.

298
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:57,350
When there is a need for oxygen  in the aircraft, the oxygen mask from the upper cabinet will fall.

299
00:20:57,350 --> 00:21:02,970
Pull the mask forward, breathe in, and attach the band to your head.

300
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:05,410
In case of cabin decompression...

301
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:11,760
Do you need anything?

302
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,920
I'm burning up, right? I have a fever.

303
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:17,720
- You don't have a fever.
- Here, over here.

304
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:19,220
Now it'll get better, right?

305
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:22,470
Please just touch all over. It's because my head hurts so much.

306
00:21:22,470 --> 00:21:25,260
My fever's going right down.

307
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,000
Ah, that feels good. It's coming down.

308
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Should I do it for you?

309
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,460
Huh?

310
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:34,900
You don't seem to have a fever. Should I push a bit harder?

311
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:38,410
What? Push what?

312
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:51,600
Unni!

313
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,010
Oh, Honey! What is all of this?

314
00:21:54,010 --> 00:21:56,360
The special deal samples.

315
00:21:56,360 --> 00:22:01,440
Where did the general manager go? Did he mention anything about meeting the special deal director or the office manager?

316
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,500
Special deal director?

317
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:07,380
I don't know about that, but he said he had something to buy so he left.

318
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:20,260
Ho Joon?

319
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:24,500
Would you please put it around your neck?

320
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:28,320
Has he gone cold ...? It's what he wants you to think before he proposes!

321
00:22:31,060 --> 00:22:34,640
Ho Joon ... perhaps ...?

322
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:47,730
Ho Joon.

323
00:22:47,730 --> 00:22:50,240
Aw, really.

324
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,000
Yes, Ho Joon?

325
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,100
I heard you came to the department store. Are you still here?

326
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:59,520
- Yes. And?
- That's good.

327
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:04,040
Then let's meet for a bit. I have something to tell you.

328
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:06,000
Right now?

329
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,420
Alright. I got it.

330
00:23:16,430 --> 00:23:19,660
I... I'm getting married.

331
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:25,650
But ... We promised we would get married.

332
00:23:25,650 --> 00:23:28,020
But why are we breaking up?

333
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:35,270
I had another woman.

334
00:23:36,460 --> 00:23:39,240
- What?
- I was going to tell you earlier...

335
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:43,340
You know my heart's weak. How could I, to you...

336
00:23:43,340 --> 00:23:48,040
I was scared so I couldn't tell you. Truthfully, in the beginning, seeing you,

337
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:52,280
I was going to clear things up. But...

338
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:55,090
She's been pregnant for three months!

339
00:23:55,090 --> 00:23:58,660
- Before her stomach gets any larger, I said we should get married.
- Hold on! Hold on a second.

340
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:02,000
So you secretly two-timed me,

341
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,780
and since that woman is now pregnant, you're going to marry her?

342
00:24:05,780 --> 00:24:08,840
- Simply, yes.
- Then...

343
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:12,060
- Then at the jewelry store too...?
- Huh?

344
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:17,360
I'm sorry, Ha Na.

345
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:24,800
Are you okay?

346
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,600
Oh, are you okay?

347
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:33,800
- Don't touch me.
- Okay.

348
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:42,180
But you might as well hit me or curse me.

349
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:44,880
You not saying anything is scarier.

350
00:25:04,450 --> 00:25:07,130
- Bad bastard.
- You could've just hit me once!

351
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:10,890
- This is cheating!
- What? Cheating?

352
00:25:10,890 --> 00:25:14,080
Did you just say cheating?

353
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:18,680
Forget it. Who is it?

354
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:20,820
- That woman.
- Huh?

355
00:25:20,820 --> 00:25:23,180
I said who is it!

356
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:29,950
I'm Yoon Min Ji from the design team.

357
00:25:29,950 --> 00:25:32,890
Yoon Min Ji is already doing a presentation?

358
00:25:32,890 --> 00:25:34,220
Hasn't it only been one year?

359
00:25:34,220 --> 00:25:38,640
Because the idea's fresh. She's our team's ace.

360
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:45,160
The shoe's design captures women's most shining, beautiful moments in their twenties.

361
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:48,460
To express the shiny, beautiful moments of those in their twenties,

362
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:51,240
we put sparkling glitter on the front, and as an extra,

363
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:54,670
made the straps thin to express femininity.

364
00:25:54,670 --> 00:25:59,250
Although it's very flashy, the ribbon added to the ankle area

365
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:01,690
expresses the beauty of those in their endearing twenties.

366
00:26:01,690 --> 00:26:08,530
And we used buckle adornments that can be seen in foreign brands to increase its elegance.

367
00:26:13,050 --> 00:26:17,150
Perhaps it is because the designer is young but these look fresh.

368
00:26:17,150 --> 00:26:20,950
- What do you think,  Chief Lee?
- It's very good. The design is unique.

369
00:26:20,950 --> 00:26:23,810
We should hear the store managers' opinions, too.

370
00:26:23,810 --> 00:26:25,990
Manager Joo, what do you think?

371
00:26:25,990 --> 00:26:32,070
I think that it's a design that women in their twenties

372
00:26:32,070 --> 00:26:34,460
prefer these days.

373
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:40,580
Team Leader Oh, what do you think?

374
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:50,940
Just tell me truthfully. Team Leader Oh's judgments are known to be spot on.

375
00:26:57,550 --> 00:27:00,200
I don't think it'll work out.

376
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,800
What?

377
00:27:03,980 --> 00:27:06,780
First, your design

378
00:27:06,780 --> 00:27:09,680
is too flashy for an ordinary twenty-something to wear.

379
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:16,040
Second, items with glitter are too expensive because of the high labor cost.

380
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:18,340
And third,

381
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:26,050
I just don't like it.

382
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:45,010
- It's over. You've worked hard, bye.
- You've worked hard.

383
00:27:45,010 --> 00:27:47,850
- Goodbye.
- I'm leaving!
- Okay!

384
00:27:53,930 --> 00:27:57,190
Stewardess Choi, please make sure to cook dinner tonight.

385
00:27:57,190 --> 00:28:00,960
I absolutely refuse to eat delivered foods such as chicken, pigs' feet, pizza and bossam, etc.

386
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:06,570
Hey, it's our MBLAQ's Mir's birthday today. Noona has to go and pay my tribute.

387
00:28:06,570 --> 00:28:09,620
- What about me?  What about me!
- Sorry!

388
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:13,680
Ah, she's really too much.

389
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,840
Assistant Purser.

390
00:28:17,150 --> 00:28:20,810
- Yes?
- I can call you Sunbae, right?

391
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:23,490
Well, sure.

392
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:27,470
Thank you for earlier, Sunbae.

393
00:28:27,470 --> 00:28:29,970
There's no need to be thankful.

394
00:28:29,970 --> 00:28:34,670
- But you should work on your courage a bit more.
- Ah, yes.

395
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:42,270
- Sunbae, for dinner perhaps...
- Hold on a second.

396
00:28:43,210 --> 00:28:45,880
Hello? Yes, Mother.

397
00:28:46,810 --> 00:28:49,140
Seaweed soup?

398
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:52,750
Stir-fried glass noodles with vegetables (japchae) too? I'll go there immediately!

399
00:28:53,570 --> 00:28:55,460
Goodbye.

